{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/vn971/rua/pulls/167", "id": 663050600, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NjYzMDUwNjAw", "html_url": "https://github.com/vn971/rua/pull/167", "diff_url": "https://github.com/vn971/rua/pull/167.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/vn971/rua/pull/167.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/vn971/rua/issues/167", "number": 167, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Generate seccomp.bpf during build", "user": {"login": "bbx0", "id": 39773919, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5NzczOTE5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39773919?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0", "html_url": "https://github.com/bbx0", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bbx0/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "This is a proposal for a runtime independent handling of the `seccomp.bpf` file. This allows support for additional architectures like `aarch64` or `arm` (see #126).\r\n\r\n#### How does it work?\r\n* A specific `seccomp.bpf` is generated via `build.rs` during compilation.\r\n  * The generated `seccomp.bpf` matches the `target_arch` of the `rua` binary. It's no longer required to distinguish different versions during runtime.\r\n  * The `seccomp.bpf` is embedded to the binary, just like the prebuilt ones before. During runtime it is extracted to `.system/seccomp.bpf`. (The prebuilt files are removed by this pull request.)\r\n* A new *build-time* dependency `libscmp` is introduced to generate the `seccomp.bpf` file.\r\n  * There are various crates available for that purpose but to me `libscmp` seems most appealing. It has a very low footprint and provides all required features (especially `seccomp_syscall_resolve_name` and `seccomp_export_bpf`). An alternative would be the `libseccomp` crate.\r\n \r\n#### How can it be tested / reviewed?\r\n* The implementation exports next to the `seccomp.bpf` a `seccomp.pfc` to `OUT_DIR` containing the human-readable output of the filter. (This second file is not embedded to the binary but can easily be inspected.)\r\n* The `md5sum` for the `seccomp.bpf` file generated by this implementation is identical to the old one generated by [seccomp](https://github.com/kurnevsky/dotfiles/blob/master/.seccomp/) (https://github.com/kurnevsky/dotfiles/commit/1432bf8ae2b62f16142b7c87ad2e0fd28d27e9fc).\r\n```sh\r\n$ find . -name \\*.bpf -exec md5sum {} \\;\r\nde85db9cf299f131c51cecee5f84ce77  ./res/seccomp-i686.bpf\r\nf9cd17bc2fe18abc4f672071dd9e0c9c  ./res/seccomp-x86_64.bpf\r\nde85db9cf299f131c51cecee5f84ce77  ./target/i686-unknown-linux-gnu/debug/build/rua-5b88deb180f14f08/out/seccomp.bpf\r\nf9cd17bc2fe18abc4f672071dd9e0c9c  ./target/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/debug/build/rua-bdd5a199bf2717e3/out/seccomp.bpf\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Remarks\r\n* The `seccomp.bpf` file can contain the ruleset for all supported architecures at once. This comes with an increased file size but may reduce the logic in `build.rs` by a few lines. (I don't think it's worth it.)\r\n\r\nI hope this helps. In case another solution fits better, I'm happy to revise.", "created_at": "2021-06-06T21:10:02Z", "updated_at": "2021-09-28T14:01:19Z", "closed_at": "2021-09-21T07:05:59Z", "merged_at": "2021-09-21T07:05:59Z", "merge_commit_sha": "37ede8299570fd31368731e7535aedff86d4f4e9", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels